WEBVTT

00:02.540 --> 00:03.790
Adult Timmy: I turned 12
in the summer of 1972 --

00:03.790 --> 00:05.000
an awesome time to be a kid.

00:05.000 --> 00:06.960
It was the Wild West.

00:06.960 --> 00:09.460
Bike helmets hadn't been
invented yet or car seatbelts

00:09.460 --> 00:12.420
or even normal
adult supervision.

00:12.420 --> 00:15.080
Dads weren't around
as much as they are now.

00:15.080 --> 00:17.750
Mine was too busy with his job
at a big defense contractor,

00:17.750 --> 00:20.670
keeping our neighborhood safe
from North Vietnamese invasion.

00:20.670 --> 00:23.250
And my mom was busy
running the house.

00:23.250 --> 00:24.830
She had a lot on her plate.

00:24.830 --> 00:26.330
Did I mention
we were Catholics?

00:26.330 --> 00:29.920
There were eight of us kids,
all boys.

00:29.920 --> 00:32.540
That was a lot of testosterone
for one house,
[ Yells ]

00:32.540 --> 00:35.120
and it was about
to become even more.

00:35.120 --> 00:36.580
I just said
that one of them

00:36.580 --> 00:37.830
would have to give up
their bed to Lawrence

00:37.830 --> 00:39.790
for the summer.
Knock it off.

00:39.790 --> 00:42.380
You are not gonna ruin
your brother's homecoming.

00:42.380 --> 00:44.880
My dad was so excited because
my oldest brother, Lawrence,

00:44.880 --> 00:47.880
filled an obligation all
big Catholic families felt --

00:47.880 --> 00:50.040
sending a son
to the seminary.

00:50.040 --> 00:52.040
♪ In a white room ♪

00:52.040 --> 00:54.170
♪ With black curtains ♪

00:54.170 --> 00:55.670
♪ In the station ♪

00:55.670 --> 00:56.960
Having a future priest

00:56.960 --> 00:58.880
was a big source of status
for our family,

00:58.880 --> 01:00.790
putting us
way ahead of the Harrigans.

01:00.790 --> 01:03.040
12 kids, and all they
came up with was a nun.

01:03.040 --> 01:05.210
♪ Tired starlings ♪

01:05.210 --> 01:06.540
But having Lawrence
back from college

01:06.540 --> 01:09.080
made me,
the needy middle child,

01:09.080 --> 01:12.080
feel more forgotten than ever.

01:12.080 --> 01:14.120
Father Dunne:
This is my body,

01:14.120 --> 01:16.170
which will be
given up for you.

01:16.880 --> 01:19.880
[ Bells ringing loudly ]

01:19.880 --> 01:23.040
That was the day I famously
decided to upstage God.

01:23.040 --> 01:24.460
[ Ringing continues ]

01:24.460 --> 01:25.920
What the hell
is wrong with that kid?

01:25.920 --> 01:27.080
♪♪

01:27.080 --> 01:29.790
[ Ringing continues ]

01:30.500 --> 01:32.120
You made a spectacle
of yourself in there.

01:32.120 --> 01:33.540
You should be
ashamed of yourself.

01:33.540 --> 01:35.250
[ Baby coos ]

01:35.250 --> 01:36.580
My family just
couldn't appreciate

01:36.580 --> 01:38.250
my lively sense of showmanship.

01:38.250 --> 01:39.710
Clearly, I would need to look

01:39.710 --> 01:42.080
for a wider,
more sophisticated audience.

01:42.080 --> 01:44.210
[ "Man of La Mancha
(I am I, Don Quixote)" plays ]

01:44.210 --> 01:45.830
Yes.

01:45.830 --> 01:47.250
Yes, I do.

01:48.420 --> 01:52.000
♪ I am I, Don Quixote ♪

01:52.000 --> 01:54.420
♪ The Lord of La Mancha ♪

01:54.420 --> 01:59.380
♪ My destiny calls, and I go ♪

01:59.380 --> 02:00.750
How's college going anyway,
college man?

02:00.750 --> 02:03.380
Uh, it's --
There's food!

02:03.380 --> 02:05.580
School's okay. I took
a math class last semester.

02:05.580 --> 02:06.790
They teach
math there, too?

02:06.790 --> 02:08.620
Hey. You're embarrassing
yourself.

02:08.620 --> 02:10.710
St. Joe's is a fully-accredited
university.

02:10.710 --> 02:12.380
You get into
Pythagoras' theorem yet?

02:12.380 --> 02:14.790
It's a hell of a theorem,
Pythagoras'.

02:14.790 --> 02:16.670
[ Chuckling ] Yeah.
I'm a fan.

02:16.670 --> 02:18.750
Bless us, O Lord,
and these, Thy gifts...

02:18.750 --> 02:20.330
All: Which we are
about to receive

02:20.330 --> 02:23.000
from Thy bounty through
Christ our Lord. Amen.

02:24.290 --> 02:26.920
-Careful.
-This ketchup tastes funny.

02:26.920 --> 02:28.790
It's only different
because Mom made it,

02:28.790 --> 02:30.170
and then she put it
in the regular bottle.

02:30.170 --> 02:31.420
Mom made the ketchup?

02:31.420 --> 02:32.750
What, His Majesty's
so fancy now

02:32.750 --> 02:35.040
he can only eat
store-bought ketchup?

02:35.040 --> 02:36.420
Lawrence, I want
to pick your brain

02:36.420 --> 02:38.540
about how young people
see our president.

02:38.540 --> 02:41.000
I find it informative
hearing all points of view.

02:41.000 --> 02:42.460
Nixon's in the pocket
of big business.

02:42.460 --> 02:43.580
Nobody asked you,
fathead.

02:43.580 --> 02:45.080
Joey, make room
for your brother.

02:45.080 --> 02:46.500
Hey, I wasn't done
with my pork chop.

02:46.500 --> 02:47.670
Eat it over the sink.

02:47.670 --> 02:49.460
I mean, is Nixon
even on the level?

02:49.460 --> 02:50.880
I mean, what about that
Watergate break-in?

02:50.880 --> 02:52.920
No, no. Nixon had nothing
to do with that.

02:52.920 --> 02:54.460
[ Music playing in background ]
You know what
I call Watergate?

02:54.460 --> 02:56.170
That's phony news.

02:56.170 --> 02:58.210
Would you tell him
to cut that racket?

02:58.210 --> 03:00.040
Sorry. I didn't mean
to upset you.

03:00.040 --> 03:02.040
I'm not upset.
You seem pretty upset.

03:02.040 --> 03:03.620
You want to stay
out of this?
You know what?

03:03.620 --> 03:07.250
I actually, uh, promised I'd
drop in and see my friend AJ,

03:07.250 --> 03:09.330
and I promised
to go right now,

03:09.330 --> 03:12.500
so I'm gonna
go get changed.

03:12.500 --> 03:15.290
Timmy:
♪ The Lord of La Mancha ♪

03:15.290 --> 03:17.040
♪ A name -- ♪
[ Record scratches ]

03:17.040 --> 03:18.040
Hey.

03:18.040 --> 03:19.580
Mom, I have to learn
these songs.

03:19.580 --> 03:20.960
Why, so you can
scare away bats?

03:20.960 --> 03:22.420
No one wants
to hear you caterwauling.

03:22.420 --> 03:24.290
What is this?
N-Nothing.

03:24.290 --> 03:25.750
Just having fun.

03:25.750 --> 03:27.040
Well, stop that.

03:29.120 --> 03:30.790
What are you
really doing?

03:30.790 --> 03:33.000
Okay, I'll tell you,
but it's a secret.

03:33.000 --> 03:34.620
I'm auditioning
for a very prestigious

03:34.620 --> 03:35.880
children's theater
in Hollywood.

03:35.880 --> 03:36.880
-Mom!
-No!

03:36.880 --> 03:38.250
Why can't I?

03:38.250 --> 03:39.750
'Cause nobody's driving you
to Hollyweird

03:39.750 --> 03:42.330
to be in some ridiculous show.
-I could take a bus

03:42.330 --> 03:44.290
or hitchhike.
You know
I don't approve that,

03:44.290 --> 03:45.830
wasting good money
on buses.

03:45.830 --> 03:47.540
Frank: [ Mockingly ] Look at me.
I'm Timmy. I'm special.

03:47.540 --> 03:49.540
Yeah, no, sorry. We do not have
the wherewithal in this family

03:49.540 --> 03:51.750
for any of you kids
to be special.

03:51.750 --> 03:53.120
And thank goodness you mostly
turned out uninteresting,

03:53.120 --> 03:54.620
like Frank here.

03:54.620 --> 03:56.920
Hey. Here's
a summer project --

03:56.920 --> 03:58.080
foreign missions.

03:58.080 --> 03:59.330
Poor pagan babies
are starving to death,

03:59.330 --> 04:00.620
and the church needs
money to save them

04:00.620 --> 04:02.460
by baptizing them
before they die.

04:02.460 --> 04:07.120
♪♪

04:11.040 --> 04:13.670
Something's yours
around here,

04:13.670 --> 04:15.580
you really got
to hold onto it, okay?

04:15.580 --> 04:20.330
♪♪

04:20.330 --> 04:22.330
Mommy, my lungs hurt.
I have asthma.

04:22.330 --> 04:23.880
No, you don't.
We can't afford asthma.

04:23.880 --> 04:26.790
That's just smog.
Go back outside and play.

04:26.790 --> 04:29.040
Going to bingo
tonight with Dad.
Ooh, he's got you

04:29.040 --> 04:31.210
wearing your collar
like his prize poodle.

04:31.210 --> 04:32.880
Hey, I don't mind you
being the favorite.

04:32.880 --> 04:34.750
It's less pressure on
the rest of us not to suck.

04:34.750 --> 04:37.040
Ah, well, I might be stepping
off the pedestal soon.

04:37.040 --> 04:38.500
I'm not just home
for the summer.

04:38.500 --> 04:39.830
I'm thinking about
not going back

04:39.830 --> 04:41.250
to the seminary
at all, man.

04:41.250 --> 04:42.580
Mike and Peggy
won't like that.

04:42.580 --> 04:44.290
Well, it's my decision,
my life.

04:44.290 --> 04:46.210
You think so?
Seriously?

04:46.210 --> 04:47.210
I'm the next in line,

04:47.210 --> 04:48.500
so if you don't
join the priesthood,

04:48.500 --> 04:50.120
they'll definitely
make me.

04:50.120 --> 04:51.460
When Notre Dame
beat Michigan State,

04:51.460 --> 04:53.250
Dad promised God
one priest.

04:53.250 --> 04:55.040
-Just tell 'em "no."
-I'm not you.

04:55.040 --> 04:58.040
I don't get to grow my hair
and argue politics with Dad.

04:58.040 --> 04:59.960
Don't do this.

04:59.960 --> 05:01.420
I've got a girlfriend now,

05:01.420 --> 05:03.620
a secret girlfriend,
and she's really cool,

05:03.620 --> 05:05.790
but not so cool that
she'll keep making out with me

05:05.790 --> 05:07.080
once I'm Father Eddie.

05:07.080 --> 05:08.540
Just tell 'em the truth.
They can handle it.

05:08.540 --> 05:11.420
No way!
Mom would wig out.

05:11.420 --> 05:12.580
[ Toilet flushing ]
Mom must never know.

05:12.580 --> 05:14.710
Then you shouldn't
talk so loudly

05:14.710 --> 05:16.790
right next
to the bathroom.
You didn't
hear a thing.

05:16.790 --> 05:18.170
Mm, I'll have
to sleep on that,

05:18.170 --> 05:20.580
tonight,
in my own bed.

05:20.580 --> 05:21.960
You'll like it
where I've been sleeping --

05:21.960 --> 05:23.120
under the dining room
table.

05:23.120 --> 05:24.830
You can still smell
where the dog died.

05:24.830 --> 05:27.000
Narc!
[ Grunts ]

05:27.000 --> 05:28.000
Aaaaah!

05:30.620 --> 05:31.790
Excuse me, Mama.

05:31.790 --> 05:33.290
You should probably know
that Frank and Edd--

05:33.290 --> 05:35.170
Eddie's
killing Frank!

05:35.170 --> 05:36.080
[ Sighs ]

05:37.540 --> 05:39.830
[ Clangs ]
Ow!

05:39.830 --> 05:41.330
[ Indistinct yelling ]

05:41.330 --> 05:43.040
As ignored as I was generally,

05:43.040 --> 05:44.420
I was absolutely invisible

05:44.420 --> 05:45.830
whenever my brothers
were fighting,

05:45.830 --> 05:48.790
so, really,
most of the time.

05:48.790 --> 05:51.750
There's...cat...poop...
in...here.

05:51.750 --> 05:52.830
Ugh!

05:54.790 --> 05:57.170
Hi, I was interested
in auditioning for your show.

05:58.290 --> 06:00.080
As the star...

06:00.080 --> 06:01.580
or some other
very large role?

06:03.040 --> 06:04.790
Performing experience?

06:04.790 --> 06:06.670
Well, uh,
nothing you'd have seen.

06:06.670 --> 06:08.040
I...

06:08.040 --> 06:10.120
Oh! I sing
the Oscar Meyer Wiener song

06:10.120 --> 06:11.790
whenever relatives
come over.

06:11.790 --> 06:12.750
It's very good.

06:12.750 --> 06:14.290
I'll explain.

06:14.290 --> 06:15.710
I heard the whole thing.
-No, stop.

06:19.120 --> 06:20.380
I should be the one
to tell them.

06:22.580 --> 06:24.170
Mom, Dad, um...

06:26.540 --> 06:29.170
...I'm thinking about
leaving the seminary,

06:29.170 --> 06:30.790
not becoming a priest.
-What?!

06:30.790 --> 06:32.040
-What?
-What?

06:32.040 --> 06:33.580
I'm sorry. I didn't hear
the priest part.

06:33.580 --> 06:35.460
All I heard about was
Eddie's secret girlfriend.

06:35.460 --> 06:37.790
I know this feels like
a big deal right now --

06:37.790 --> 06:39.670
Eddie has
a secret girlfriend?

06:39.670 --> 06:41.080
♪♪

06:45.080 --> 06:46.330
Peggy: How long has this
been going on?

06:46.330 --> 06:47.500
I've been weighing the decision
for a while now.

06:47.500 --> 06:48.250
I was talking about
Eddie's girlfriend.

06:48.250 --> 06:49.210
I'd like
to meet this person.

06:49.210 --> 06:50.710
I seriously hate you.

06:50.710 --> 06:52.170
I already knew you
were up to something.

06:52.170 --> 06:54.040
Remember,
I do your laundry.

06:54.040 --> 06:55.460
[ Whimpers ]

06:55.460 --> 06:57.120
What are you planning on
studying instead?

06:57.120 --> 06:58.710
Me, for starters.
"Me."

06:58.710 --> 06:59.790
And not
in any classroom,

06:59.790 --> 07:01.880
but out experiencing
the world, you know?

07:01.880 --> 07:03.460
M-Maybe I'll backpack
across Europe.

07:03.460 --> 07:05.580
I backpacked across Europe
when I was your age,

07:05.580 --> 07:07.750
except there were Germans
shooting at me.

07:07.750 --> 07:10.290
You were actually younger,
and you forged Grandpa's
signature to enlist

07:10.290 --> 07:11.460
because you believed in
what you were doing.

07:11.460 --> 07:13.120
Hey, you want
to kill Germans?

07:13.120 --> 07:14.670
I'll sign the papers
right now.

07:14.670 --> 07:16.380
Lawrence
isn't killing any Germans!

07:16.380 --> 07:18.290
He's gonna be a priest!
Or somebody is.

07:18.290 --> 07:20.290
If not him, Eddie for sure.
-[ Sighs ]

07:20.290 --> 07:21.960
Right now, you need to
get down to that church
and help Father Dunne.

07:21.960 --> 07:23.750
The man has diabetes!

07:23.750 --> 07:26.330
You're right.
I made a commitment,

07:26.330 --> 07:27.540
a word that you might
want to look up

07:27.540 --> 07:29.210
in that new
collegiate dictionary

07:29.210 --> 07:31.420
that we had to buy you
for 22 bucks

07:31.420 --> 07:34.330
because our old dictionary
didn't contain hip new lingo

07:34.330 --> 07:36.380
like "Congressperson"
and "gorp."

07:37.710 --> 07:39.580
I will see you...

07:39.580 --> 07:40.920
at bingo.

07:40.920 --> 07:44.830
♪♪

07:44.830 --> 07:46.460
And get a haircut!

07:46.460 --> 07:48.620
♪♪

07:48.620 --> 07:49.790
[ Door slams ]

07:49.790 --> 07:52.790
♪♪

07:52.790 --> 07:53.830
It was that easy.

07:53.830 --> 07:55.790
One phone call,

07:55.790 --> 07:58.170
and I found my first paying
show-business job --

07:58.170 --> 08:00.500
"paying" meaning I had to pay.

08:00.500 --> 08:01.500
[ Sighs ]

08:01.500 --> 08:03.170
[ Box rattles ]

08:04.330 --> 08:05.620
[ Coins clatter ]

08:05.620 --> 08:07.540
I had more money than this.

08:07.540 --> 08:09.710
Joey: You had 9 bucks,
an Abba-Zaba,

08:09.710 --> 08:11.290
and a picture...

08:11.290 --> 08:14.250
of Laurie Partridge.

08:14.250 --> 08:15.670
What happened
to my money, Joey?

08:15.670 --> 08:17.880
I saw Jethro Tull at The Forum
on Saturday.

08:17.880 --> 08:20.170
That man don't blow
his flute for free.

08:20.170 --> 08:21.750
I have
an audition tomorrow!

08:21.750 --> 08:23.710
It costs 40 bucks!

08:23.710 --> 08:24.880
Take a chill pill.

08:25.830 --> 08:27.080
Hang on.

08:30.080 --> 08:33.000
Let's reconvene where there's
a modicum of privacy.

08:33.000 --> 08:34.170
10 minutes, in my office.

08:35.380 --> 08:37.540
Bring ice.

08:37.540 --> 08:38.620
[ Door closes ]

08:38.620 --> 08:40.080
[ Grunts ]

08:40.080 --> 08:41.540
[ The Kinks'
"You Really Got Me" plays ]

08:41.540 --> 08:45.210
I've given some thought
to your money problem.

08:45.210 --> 08:47.540
My problem is
you stealing my money.

08:47.540 --> 08:49.000
You're really going
to have to let that go.

08:50.670 --> 08:52.710
My suggestion is

08:52.710 --> 08:53.830
take your little
mission box

08:53.830 --> 08:55.290
up to the rich,
douchebag neighborhood

08:55.290 --> 08:57.290
and ring
a few douchebag doors.

08:57.290 --> 08:59.000
With your big brown eyes
and big round head,

08:59.000 --> 09:00.710
you'll clear 40 bucks
in an hour.

09:00.710 --> 09:02.420
That money's
for the pagan babies.

09:02.420 --> 09:04.040
Rich people don't care.

09:04.040 --> 09:05.960
They get off on giving
their dough away.

09:05.960 --> 09:07.920
They just want to feel good
about themselves

09:07.920 --> 09:10.120
and get you
the hell off their porch.

09:10.120 --> 09:12.000
A normal family, I could
just ask Mom or Dad,

09:12.000 --> 09:14.460
but Dad's too cheap.

09:14.460 --> 09:18.500
If he could, Dad would enjoy
tossing his dough around,

09:18.500 --> 09:20.790
taking us all out to
a Ponderosa Steakhouse, say,

09:20.790 --> 09:23.210
or Sizzler.

09:23.210 --> 09:24.920
But that
Great Depression thing

09:24.920 --> 09:26.420
always kicks in,
and, instead,

09:26.420 --> 09:29.330
we come home to the taste
of fried bologna

09:29.330 --> 09:30.580
and sadness.

09:32.250 --> 09:33.790
Okay, blow.
I got things to do.

09:33.790 --> 09:35.500
Dad let Joey build a tree house

09:35.500 --> 09:37.880
because he liked that
Joey wanted to use his hands.

09:37.880 --> 09:40.080
He had no idea how much.

09:40.080 --> 09:42.080
♪ You really got me ♪

09:42.080 --> 09:42.960
♪ You really -- ♪

09:42.960 --> 09:45.750
Look --
No more holes.

09:45.750 --> 09:47.080
And so groovy.

09:47.080 --> 09:48.120
You'd be right at home
at a love-in.

09:50.500 --> 09:52.120
Hey, that's the style
these days.

09:52.120 --> 09:53.960
Trust me -- ratty dungarees
with patches.

09:53.960 --> 09:56.290
Well, you
certainly get it.

09:56.290 --> 09:59.500
Mom, this is
my girlfriend, Wendi.

09:59.500 --> 10:00.500
Girlfriend.

10:02.210 --> 10:04.380
Eddie has a girlfriend.
[ Chuckles ]

10:04.380 --> 10:06.210
How come?
I'm sorry?

10:06.210 --> 10:07.420
Oh, no need
to be sorry.

10:07.420 --> 10:09.830
Look, I love Eddie.
Well, I love all my boys.

10:09.830 --> 10:13.250
I have to. But how on earth
would Eddie get a girlfriend?

10:13.250 --> 10:15.040
Lots of kids our age
are going together.

10:15.040 --> 10:17.250
Yeah, but not
with Eddie.

10:17.250 --> 10:18.710
How long have you two
known each other?

10:18.710 --> 10:21.380
A-Around four months.
Ah, see,
that explains it.

10:21.380 --> 10:23.170
I always say it takes
four and a half months

10:23.170 --> 10:25.460
before you really see
the flaws in a person.

10:25.460 --> 10:26.670
Now you can move on
to some other boy,

10:26.670 --> 10:28.210
and I just
saved you two weeks.

10:29.580 --> 10:30.830
[ Sewing machine whirring ]

10:30.830 --> 10:33.330
I think you are
amazing, Mrs. Cleary.

10:33.330 --> 10:36.420
Running this home is a huge
managerial achievement.

10:36.420 --> 10:39.750
Modern women look up to
Indira Gandhi and Golda Meir,

10:39.750 --> 10:41.670
but those who choose
a domestic career

10:41.670 --> 10:43.460
are no less viable
a role model.

10:45.380 --> 10:47.120
[ Sewing machine turns off ]
[ Chuckles ]

10:47.120 --> 10:49.790
I mean, that's just silly.
I'm no role model.

10:49.790 --> 10:52.670
Though, I would like to see
Golda handle all my housework

10:52.670 --> 10:55.290
and still make franks and beans
for Mister Meir.

10:55.290 --> 10:57.290
You're so slim, Wendi.

10:57.290 --> 10:59.170
I'm gonna make you a shift.

10:59.170 --> 11:02.380
I have this Dacron fabric.
It is so colorful.

11:02.380 --> 11:04.880
It's like
an LSD acid trip.

11:04.880 --> 11:07.250
I wouldn't know.
Correct answer.

11:07.250 --> 11:08.790
Come with me.
Let's take your measurements.

11:08.790 --> 11:11.120
♪♪

11:11.120 --> 11:12.460
Good night.

11:12.460 --> 11:16.960
♪♪

11:16.960 --> 11:18.120
Thank you so much,
ma'am,

11:18.120 --> 11:19.750
on behalf of
the foreign missions.

11:19.750 --> 11:22.170
So, listen,

11:22.170 --> 11:23.710
there's another
good cause I wondered

11:23.710 --> 11:25.620
if you might give to.
Um...

11:25.620 --> 11:28.830
I've always had this dream of
singing and dancing in shows.

11:33.290 --> 11:35.580
I-17.

11:35.580 --> 11:37.620
I-17.

11:37.620 --> 11:39.620
As in what you never want
to hear the girl say.

11:39.620 --> 11:41.040
[ Softly ] "I 17."

11:41.040 --> 11:42.790
[ Laughter ]
Good luck to you.

11:46.790 --> 11:48.790
You came.

11:48.790 --> 11:50.290
I'm glad.

11:50.290 --> 11:51.540
[ Normal voice ]
Oh, I've spotted
Lawrence Cleary,

11:51.540 --> 11:53.580
our handsome seminarian.

11:53.580 --> 11:55.380
Mike, could you have your son
call some numbers

11:55.380 --> 11:57.000
and give
this old voice a rest?

11:57.000 --> 11:58.880
[ Applause ]

11:58.880 --> 12:01.620
Back off, girls.
That part of his life is over.

12:01.620 --> 12:03.420
[ Laughter ]

12:06.880 --> 12:08.210
Okay.

12:08.210 --> 12:09.540
G-50.

12:09.540 --> 12:11.830
As in, "Gee, where have
the last 50 years gone?"

12:11.830 --> 12:13.250
Well, I'll tell you
where they went.

12:13.250 --> 12:15.080
Me calling
bingo numbers. Whoo!

12:15.080 --> 12:16.750
[ Laughter ]

12:21.460 --> 12:24.540
I-20.
That would be I-20.

12:27.000 --> 12:28.330
I-20.

12:30.040 --> 12:32.960
As in I am 20,

12:32.960 --> 12:35.290
which means I'm an adult.

12:35.290 --> 12:37.710
But am I really an adult
if I can't even stand up

12:37.710 --> 12:39.880
for who I am
and what I want to be?

12:39.880 --> 12:42.080
Dad, I'm sorry.
I don't want to be a priest,

12:42.080 --> 12:43.750
and I'm dropping out
of the seminary.

12:43.750 --> 12:45.380
[ Murmuring ]

12:48.080 --> 12:49.920
[ Bell rings ]
Woman: Bingo!

12:54.380 --> 12:55.580
He's quitting, and he said it
in front of the whole bingo.

12:55.580 --> 12:57.380
There is no putting
the toothpaste back in the tube.

12:57.380 --> 12:58.750
Don't be silly.

12:58.750 --> 13:00.830
I've been refilling
that same Pepsodent for years.

13:00.830 --> 13:02.080
I don't get it.

13:02.080 --> 13:03.460
Priesthood
was always his idea

13:03.460 --> 13:05.330
since he was little,
not mine.

13:05.330 --> 13:06.500
Remember
his 10th birthday

13:06.500 --> 13:07.960
where all he asked for
was a chalice?

13:07.960 --> 13:09.830
[ Chuckles softly ]

13:09.830 --> 13:11.210
How'd you leave things
with him?

13:11.210 --> 13:12.790
Ah, he's staying
with his friend AJ.

13:12.790 --> 13:15.000
And where
does he live?
Don't know.
Don't care.

13:15.000 --> 13:17.040
Frank: In Burbank,
across from Shafer Field.

13:17.040 --> 13:18.580
Thanks. Okay.

13:18.580 --> 13:20.790
After work, you go
make things right with him.

13:20.790 --> 13:22.120
You're telling me
what to do now?

13:22.120 --> 13:23.710
I am,
when you're being dumb.

13:23.710 --> 13:25.250
Mike, I know I'm not up
on current events

13:25.250 --> 13:27.170
like Nixon
a-a-and Pythagoras,

13:27.170 --> 13:30.500
but I am smart when it comes
to this house and these kids.

13:30.500 --> 13:32.000
Some might even say
I'm a role model.

13:32.000 --> 13:33.960
Who might say that?
Some!

13:33.960 --> 13:35.880
There's a whole generation gap
happening out there,

13:35.880 --> 13:37.790
which I know more about 'cause
I watch "Sonny and Cher,"

13:37.790 --> 13:40.500
but I will not have any gaps
in my house with my boys.

13:42.170 --> 13:43.710
[ Sighs ] The truth is,
I never really cared

13:43.710 --> 13:45.210
about Lawrence
being a priest.

13:45.210 --> 13:46.790
I don't care what
any of my kids do,

13:46.790 --> 13:48.960
as long as --
I know, "as long
as they're happy."

13:48.960 --> 13:50.330
Oh, I don't even care
about them being happy.

13:50.330 --> 13:52.210
I just want them around.

13:52.210 --> 13:55.080
They'll scatter to
the four winds soon enough.

13:55.080 --> 13:57.580
I won't have you pushing
one of them out the door.

13:57.580 --> 14:02.080
♪♪

14:02.080 --> 14:03.380
[ Clears throat ] I'll take it
under advisement.

14:06.460 --> 14:08.460
I might go for a drive
after work tonight.

14:11.670 --> 14:14.170
Clear my head.

14:14.170 --> 14:16.710
No particular
destination.

14:16.710 --> 14:18.620
Frank:
Across from Shafer Field.
Shut up.

14:19.580 --> 14:21.290
[ Humming tune of "Man of
La Mancha (I, Don Quixote)" ]

14:23.670 --> 14:25.250
I'm off
to save more souls.

14:25.250 --> 14:26.540
You're not
going anywhere...

14:28.960 --> 14:30.330
without your mission box.

14:30.330 --> 14:32.960
Nice work.
There's a lot of money there.

14:32.960 --> 14:34.830
Now, I know this wasn't
the summer you pictured,

14:34.830 --> 14:37.580
but you did well,
and honestly, Timmy,

14:37.580 --> 14:39.620
if you had any talent at all,
I think I would've noticed.

14:39.620 --> 14:41.750
Thanks, Mom.
I should go.

14:41.750 --> 14:43.620
Hey, bring William
with you, okay?

14:43.620 --> 14:45.000
You haven't ventured
outside in days.

14:45.000 --> 14:47.420
You're gonna
get rickets.

14:47.420 --> 14:48.960
Mommy?

14:48.960 --> 14:50.710
Will I get
rickets, too?

14:50.710 --> 14:52.500
Oh, Pat...

14:52.500 --> 14:53.540
maybe.

14:55.040 --> 14:56.040
[ Doorbell buzzes ]

14:57.620 --> 15:00.790
Lawrence,
I think it's your dad.

15:00.790 --> 15:03.250
I guess there's no pretending
you're AJ's mom.

15:06.290 --> 15:07.620
[ Sighs ]

15:07.620 --> 15:09.290
Frank:
Mom, Timmy's not out

15:09.290 --> 15:11.040
collecting for
the foreign missions.

15:11.040 --> 15:12.380
He's auditioning
for the stupid show

15:12.380 --> 15:14.170
you told him not to.

15:14.170 --> 15:15.620
That kid
is a mental case.

15:15.620 --> 15:17.170
And, Frank,

15:17.170 --> 15:19.080
about you being such
a big tattle-tale --

15:19.080 --> 15:20.380
Thank you.

15:20.380 --> 15:22.580
Eddie, watch the baby!
Frank, keys.

15:22.580 --> 15:23.580
[ Door opens, keys jingle ]

15:24.960 --> 15:27.000
[ Siren wailing ]

15:28.620 --> 15:30.210
William.

15:30.210 --> 15:31.750
Am I
a good singer?

15:31.750 --> 15:34.670
No, but
confidence helps.

15:34.670 --> 15:36.750
You really seem
to have a lot of it.

15:36.750 --> 15:38.330
God only knows why.

15:41.000 --> 15:44.500
And with one tug of a
disarmingly sticky door handle,

15:44.500 --> 15:47.330
I took my first step
into show business.

15:47.620 --> 15:49.880
[ Brakes squeal ]

15:49.880 --> 15:51.670
[ Engine turns off ]

15:51.670 --> 15:53.120
Lawrence: What are we
doing out here?

15:53.120 --> 15:54.880
You know
a lot of people saw me

15:54.880 --> 15:56.080
get in the car
with you, right?

15:58.290 --> 16:00.710
You quit the seminary
over a girl?

16:00.710 --> 16:03.120
No. AJ's a recent
development.

16:03.120 --> 16:04.670
I don't even know what's going
on there, to be honest.

16:04.670 --> 16:06.120
Oh, don't worry.
She'll figure it out

16:06.120 --> 16:07.710
and tell you.

16:07.710 --> 16:08.830
[ Chuckles ]

16:08.830 --> 16:11.620
You know, this isn't
about celibacy, Dad.

16:11.620 --> 16:13.380
There are big changes
right now, and I want

16:13.380 --> 16:15.380
to be a part of them.
Hey, trust me, I know
about the changes, okay?

16:17.120 --> 16:19.540
Your mother watches
"Sonny and Cher."

16:19.540 --> 16:21.120
[ Sighs ] Look, you've been
jerking our chain

16:21.120 --> 16:23.580
about this priest thing
for years, all right?

16:23.580 --> 16:25.460
And maybe...

16:25.460 --> 16:27.500
I got excited

16:27.500 --> 16:30.500
because
it's respectable.

16:30.500 --> 16:32.080
It's certainly a step up
for the Clearys.
[ Sighs ]

16:34.330 --> 16:37.000
My dad worked his whole life
in a coal mine.

16:37.000 --> 16:38.380
That man
never had two --

16:38.380 --> 16:40.000
Whoa.

16:40.000 --> 16:41.380
Whoa!

16:41.380 --> 16:44.580
There she is --
the LGM Minuteman III.

16:44.580 --> 16:46.040
Wait, it's going
to the moon?

16:46.040 --> 16:48.500
Yeah, we're sending a nuclear
warhead to blow up the moon.

16:48.500 --> 16:50.880
We're fed up with tides
and women's periods.

16:50.880 --> 16:51.750
[ Clicks tongue ]

16:51.750 --> 16:54.080
It's a test.

16:54.080 --> 16:56.920
She'll ditch in the ocean
800 miles that way,

16:56.920 --> 16:58.750
maybe take out
a few sea otters.

16:58.750 --> 17:00.920
You know, for something
so dreadful,

17:00.920 --> 17:03.960
which I abhor
on principle,

17:03.960 --> 17:05.380
it's pretty cool.

17:07.000 --> 17:08.540
Did you build it?

17:08.540 --> 17:12.000
[ Chuckles ]
Son, I am a machinist.

17:12.000 --> 17:13.290
Engineers, the scientists,

17:13.290 --> 17:15.540
they figure out
what they need.

17:15.540 --> 17:17.710
I grind a few pieces
on a lathe --

17:17.710 --> 17:19.290
grommets,
some sheeting.

17:19.290 --> 17:21.170
They're down there
right now,

17:21.170 --> 17:24.000
my bosses,
the big brains

17:24.000 --> 17:26.080
that took us
to the moon, and...

17:26.080 --> 17:27.920
they own the future.

17:27.920 --> 17:30.830
I'm just a guy
holding their coats...

17:30.830 --> 17:32.210
because I didn't
go to college.

17:34.830 --> 17:37.330
Look, if you are

17:37.330 --> 17:38.790
determined to quit
the seminary...

17:42.080 --> 17:45.710
...might I suggest some version
of a college degree?

17:47.920 --> 17:51.290
My father,
Michael Lawrence Cleary,

17:51.290 --> 17:54.210
he scratched at the earth
for a living.

17:54.210 --> 17:56.120
I want my sons
reaching for the stars.

18:02.250 --> 18:03.420
You know...

18:05.750 --> 18:08.420
...there's a tiny fixed nozzle
with the TVC system

18:08.420 --> 18:10.880
on the third-stage booster
when it separates.

18:12.580 --> 18:15.380
It's just
a few centimeters.

18:15.380 --> 18:18.120
It has to hold up
against 400,000 PSI.

18:21.750 --> 18:23.920
There you go.

18:23.920 --> 18:25.710
I made that nozzle.

18:25.710 --> 18:27.830
♪♪

18:27.830 --> 18:29.210
Screw it. [ Sighs ]

18:29.210 --> 18:30.620
Let's get some waffles.

18:32.000 --> 18:34.250
Our revels
now are ended.

18:34.250 --> 18:36.500
These are our actors.

18:36.500 --> 18:39.790
The solemn temple,
the great Globe itself,

18:39.790 --> 18:41.380
yea, all which
it inherits...

18:41.380 --> 18:42.830
Maybe you can get
your 40 bucks back.

18:44.120 --> 18:46.080
[ Sirens wailing ]

18:49.120 --> 18:51.330
Peggy: Oh, those sneakers
look like Eddie's size.

18:51.330 --> 18:52.710
We should come back later
with a ladder.

18:56.250 --> 18:58.540
Okay. Next up is...

18:58.540 --> 19:00.170
Timmy Cleary.

19:01.620 --> 19:03.170
[ Chair creaks ]

19:05.710 --> 19:07.460
Do you have
sheet music?

19:07.460 --> 19:09.710
Never mind.
Just, uh...

19:09.710 --> 19:11.170
You'll be fine.

19:16.250 --> 19:18.830
[ Quietly ]
♪ Sing ♪

19:18.830 --> 19:21.920
♪ Sing a song ♪

19:21.920 --> 19:25.000
♪ Sing out loud ♪

19:25.000 --> 19:27.080
♪ Sing out strong ♪

19:29.830 --> 19:32.000
♪ Sing of good things ♪

19:32.000 --> 19:34.000
♪ Not bad ♪

19:35.920 --> 19:38.710
♪ Sing of happy ♪

19:38.710 --> 19:40.830
♪ Not sad ♪

19:43.000 --> 19:44.710
♪ Sing ♪

19:44.710 --> 19:48.120
[ Piano accompanies ]
♪ Sing a song ♪

19:48.120 --> 19:50.250
[ Louder ]
♪ Make it simple ♪

19:50.250 --> 19:55.000
♪ To last
your whole life long ♪

19:55.000 --> 19:58.170
♪ Don't worry that
it's not good enough ♪

19:58.170 --> 20:01.420
♪ For anyone else to hear ♪

20:01.420 --> 20:04.210
♪ Just sing ♪

20:04.210 --> 20:08.380
♪ Sing a song ♪

20:08.380 --> 20:10.880
[ Confidently ]
♪ Sing ♪

20:10.880 --> 20:13.750
♪ Sing a song ♪

20:13.750 --> 20:16.830
♪ Let the world ♪

20:16.830 --> 20:19.080
♪ Sing along ♪

20:19.080 --> 20:20.620
[ Whispering ]
Okay, we should go.

20:20.620 --> 20:22.080
[ Whispering ] But -- But what
about Timmy disobeying?

20:22.080 --> 20:23.960
What about him
wasting 40 --
He's excellent.

20:27.170 --> 20:30.000
♪ Sing for you and ♪

20:30.000 --> 20:33.210
♪ For me ♪

20:33.210 --> 20:35.880
♪ Sing ♪

20:35.880 --> 20:39.000
People remember the 1970s
as a tense and divisive time

20:39.000 --> 20:40.880
with war and Watergate

20:40.880 --> 20:43.330
and the generations
pulling against each other,

20:43.330 --> 20:45.420
but I think back
on my ridiculous family,

20:45.420 --> 20:47.460
and it gives me hope for today

20:47.460 --> 20:49.620
that tense times are something
we just have to go through

20:49.620 --> 20:51.330
once in a while
to come out the other side

20:51.330 --> 20:53.830
a changed,
more accepting world.

20:53.830 --> 20:57.500
♪ Sing a song! ♪

21:02.000 --> 21:03.040
Time to try on
your pantaloons, milord.

21:03.040 --> 21:04.580
It's stupid going
to all this trouble.

21:04.580 --> 21:06.460
He's the understudy.
-An excellent understudy.

21:06.460 --> 21:08.210
You heard him sing.
He's practically an Osmond.

21:08.210 --> 21:10.460
I'm a heartbeat away
from the star.
And anything
could happen.

21:10.460 --> 21:12.170
That boy could get sick
or he could fall

21:12.170 --> 21:13.460
and break a leg on the way
to rehearsal.

21:13.460 --> 21:14.500
And if no one
else was around,

21:14.500 --> 21:15.880
who's to say
if he fell or got pushed.

21:15.880 --> 21:18.250
Right, Joey?
-Kid sounds like a klutz to me.

21:18.250 --> 21:19.710
You'll need
to point him out.

21:19.710 --> 21:22.000
Timmy:
♪ I am I, Don Quixote ♪

21:22.000 --> 21:24.420
♪ The Lord of La Mancha ♪

21:24.420 --> 21:26.790
♪ A name all the world
soon will -- ♪
